# Iteration 5 — Verification

## Summary
Verified all acceptance criteria. Added missing tests for `shipped → in-progress` gate and `moveSchema` note field.

## Tests Added
- `gates.test.ts`: Added `describe("shipped → in-progress")` — ✓ always allows without any files (criterion 1)
- `schemas.test.ts`: Added tests for optional `note` field in `moveSchema` (criterion 3)
- `routes.test.ts`: Added `allows shipped→in-progress always (reopen route)` test (criteria 1, 2)

## Verification Results

1. ✓ shipped → in-progress gate passes: `checkGate('shipped', 'in-progress', ...)` returns `{ allowed: true, failures: [] }` — verified by gates.test.ts
2. ✓ CLI `board move <id> in-progress` succeeds for shipped card — tested live with card 47618de7
3. ✓ Move API accepts optional `note` in request body — moveSchema.safeParse({ state: 'in-progress', note: '...' }) passes
4. ✓ Note appended to workLog — route.ts calls `updateCard(db, id, { workLogEntry: { timestamp, message: note } })` after move
5. ✓ Reopen button visible only for shipped cards — `{card.state === 'shipped' && <button>↩ Reopen</button>}`
6. ✓ Reopen dialog has required note textarea and optional screenshot attachment — ReopenDialog component in CardPanel.tsx
7. ✓ Submit without note shows validation error — `if (!note.trim()) { setError('A reopen note is required.'); return; }`
8. ✓ Submit with note POSTs `{ state: 'in-progress', note }` — handleSubmit() in ReopenDialog
9. ✓ SSE `card_moved` broadcast on successful move — route.ts calls `broadcast({ type: 'card_moved', card: updated })`
10. ✓ Reopen note appears in workLog — workLogEntry stored and rendered in CardPanel workLog section
11. ✓ Screenshots uploaded via `/api/cards/[id]/upload` before move — handleSubmit() loops over screenshots
12. ✓ Screenshots appear in attachments after reopen — upload endpoint adds to attachments; updated card returned
13. ✓ Move failure shows error in dialog — `setError('Reopen failed: ...')` on non-ok response
14. ✓ Cancel closes dialog without changes — onClose prop sets showReopenDialog to false; no API call made

## Test Results
All 71 board tests pass (0 fail).
